About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love this luggage set. I thought it was going to be nice but it is gorgeous. The stitching is perfect, no stains, smooth and just got me saying wow. All three luggage pieces have so many secret compartments especially the smallest one. I cannot wait to take this on my vacation. And the smaller one also has wheels too so you can pull that one in case you don't want to carry it. The two bigger ones also comes with their own separate keys but the biggest one key sticks a little bit, but I figured out you just have to jiggle it a little bit and it will unlock. I would recommend you get this set for this price it will blow your mind.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Cheap, arrived broken
reviews.reviewText: Welp, there's no nice way to put it. This is the cheapest suitcase I've ever seen. It arrived damaged, with the handle of the big suitcase smashed and would not extend. In order to return I would have to purchase a box from UPS, which would equate to a large portion of the item itself. I asked Amazon to make an exception, and give me a cost free return and they would not. If you decide to but this, prepare to make it one trip, maybe, and then replacing this item.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive cute solution for car trips. Won't make it through O'Hare LAX or even Love Field.
reviews.reviewText: First impression visual: This is really cute, and I like the leopard print. As a rule of thumb animal print tends to look cheap, but this is a little understated and nice. Texture of exterior is nice canvas feel.What you get: There are three pieces, a large check in, a smaller carry on, and the 22" duffle bag. The duffle actually has wheels and a handle that pulls out. The duffle is heavy enough that you will likely need to use this feature when it is loaded. I missed that in the reviews and am disappointed as I thought it'd be a cute light weight duffle for more daily use.Quality of product: Most important to know: The material is backed by plastic coating, but overall is rather thin. My suspicion is anything of weight being tossed onto it will cause a puncture. Also, the interior frame structure is minimal at best. I can absolutely see all three of these bags getting destroyed by ground crew. I like the look of it and the interior storage is ok. Since I bought as an Amazon return for only $53 I actually considered adding heavy corrugated plastic to the back of the back behind the zipper to help avoid punctures.Overall Assessment: This should work as a car trip set, but I am concerned about it holding up to baggage handlers. I am considering returning as I bought for upcoming flight and already have car trip luggage.
